---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Omar Maaouane Veiga" description="A bit about Omar Maaouane Veiga — data-driven engineer based in London.">
  <section class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <!-- ── Hero gallery ── -->
    <div class="gallery">
      <div class="gallery-item">
        <img src="/media/Sigma_Patagonia.jpg" alt="Omar in Patagonia" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <div class="gallery-item">
        <img src="/media/RIAT_Typhoon.jpg" alt="Typhoon at RIAT airshow" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <div class="gallery-item">
        <img src="/media/uni_pic.jpg" alt="University days" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <div class="gallery-item">
        <img src="/media/WS_Bro_Pic.jpg" alt="With the bro" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <div class="gallery-item">
        <img src="/media/WS_Mandem.jpg" alt="The mandem" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <div class="gallery-item">
        <img src="/media/WS_Pic_System.jpg" alt="Working on systems" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <div class="gallery-item">
        <img src="/media/WS_Pic.jpg" alt="Omar at work" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-content">
      <p>
        I'm Omar Maaouane Veiga, a London-based engineer with a background in robotics
        and a strong passion for solving problems through data. I enjoy working on
        systems that take in messy, real-world information and turn it into something
        useful, whether that system lives in software, hardware, or somewhere in
        between.
      </p>

      <p>
        It started with robotics; building things that sense the world and do
        something about it. Turns out that same thinking works just as well when
        the "robot" is a dashboard and the "action" is a human going
        <em>"oh, that's what's going on."</em> So now I do both.
      </p>

      <p>
        For me it doesn't matter which discipline it is. I'm hungry for knowledge
        and the world is my buffet 😋.
      </p>

      <h2>What I work with</h2>

      <p>
        I could list off technologies and projects all day but it'd be faster to just say that
        I'm a computer nerd with a big taste in practical electronics. Yes I code, but I also solder
        things together into inventions that make use of that code.
      </p>

      <p>
        Python is my go-to for wrangling data. If something needs a backend, an API,
        or just a script that saves someone three hours a week, I'll build it. And if
        the problem lives in the physical world — sensors, motors, embedded boards —
        even better I'll usually switch over to C++.
      </p>

      <h2>How I work</h2>

      <p>
        Honestly? I just talk to people. Over half the job is figuring out what someone
        actually needs versus what they think they need. Once that's clear, I move
        fast, keep things simple, and try not to build anything that needs a manual
        to understand. An intuitive product is a product that makes all of this fancy tech
        actually of use to anybody other than me after all.
      </p>

      <h2>Beyond work</h2>

      <p>
        When I'm not neck-deep in code or circuits, I'm probably tinkering with some
        side project that caught my eye, folding origami, modelling characters in
        Blender, or even geeking out over fighter jets at an airshow.
        I like building things, breaking things, and figuring out how things work.
        That's basically the whole personality.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>

      <p>
        If any of this sounds like your kind of conversation, I'm always up for a
        chat. Drop me an email or find me on LinkedIn — I don't bite.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* ── Photo gallery (CSS columns masonry) ── */
  .gallery {
    columns: 3;
    column-gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .gallery-item {
    break-inside: avoid;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .gallery-item img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: transform 0.4s ease, filter 0.4s ease;
    filter: grayscale(20%);
  }

  .gallery-item:hover img {
    transform: scale(1.03);
    filter: grayscale(0%);
  }

  /* ── About content ── */
  .about-content {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-content ul {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .gallery {
      columns: 2;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .gallery {
      columns: 1;
    }
  }
</style>
